@alexhung, yes I will work on getting the format and extensibility points documented. 

One clarifying note: get_action is called once for every distinct "run" name in the ruleset definition. get_action should return a function of the form `fn(c)` the function returned will be called every time a rule leading to the "run" name is resolved. In the example below, get_action will be called two times, one for "suspect" and one for "fraud". The function returned for "suspect" is going to be called every time the state machine moves to the "suspect" state. The function returned for "fraud" will be called every time the state machine moves to the "fraud" state.

```javascript
{
    "start": {
        "trigger": {
            "all":[{
                "m": {"$gt":{"amount":100}}
            }],
            "to": "suspect",
            "run": "suspect"
         }
    },
    "suspect": {
        "trigger": {
            "all":[{
                "m": {"$gt":{"amount":1000}}
            }],
            "to": "fraud",
            "run": "fraud"
        }
    },
    "fraud":{}
}
```

