Related discussion:
https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/jpmml/X1tUOdTDwY0

In brief, the JPMML-Evaluator library currently maintains category levels as `java.lang.String`. If the `DataField` element defines category levels as `"0"` and `"1"`, but the `RegressionTable` element defines category levels as `"0.0"` and `"1.0"` then, according to `String#equals(String)` they are not "the same thing".

The solution is to unify category levels across all elements. Would be trivial to implement using the Visitor API:
```Java
PMML pmml = ...

Visitor visitor = new org.jpmml.model.visitors.AbstractVisitor(){
  @Override
  public VisitorAction visit(RegressionTable regressionTable){
    String targetCategory = regressionTable.getTargetCategory();
    if(targetCategory.endsWith(".0")){
      targetCategory = targetCategory.substring(0, targetCategory.length() - ".0".length());
      regressionTable.setTargetCategory(targetCategory);
    }
    return super.visit(regressionTable);
  }
};

visitor.applyTo(pmml);
```

Alternatively, you might update `DataField/Value` elements, and append ".0" there.

