A perhaps more re-usable approach would be to use a custom field.

```python
from marshmallow import fields

class JSON(fields.Dict):

    def _deserialize(self, value, attr, data):
        decoded = json.loads(value)
        return super()._deserialize(decoded, attr, data)

    def _serialize(self, value, attr, obj):
        ret = super()._serialize(value, attr, obj)
        return json.dumps(ret)
```

Which you could use like so:

```python

import json
from marshmallow import Schema, ValidationError

class MySchema(Schema):
    props = JSON(required=False, validate=[validate_props])


sch = MySchema(strict=True)

data = {'props': json.dumps({'foo': 9})}

try:
    res = sch.load(data)
except ValidationError as err:
    print('invalid')
    print(err.data)
else:
    print('valid')
    print(res.data)
```

The output will be:

```
invalid
{'props': '{"foo": 9}'}
```

Hope this meets your use case. 

